82852>>>>>// The cConnection class is the new SQL connections class for DF 19.
82852>>>>>// If an object of the cConnection class hasn't been instantiated we use a "dummy" class in its place.
82852>>>>>
82852>>>>>// We're making references to this object handle so we need it defined
82852>>>>>// here as well as for the cDbUpdateHandler class
82852>>>>>
82852>>>>>    Global_Variable Handle ghoSQLConnectionHandler
82852>>>>>    
82852>>>>>Class cSQLConnectionHandler is a cObject  
82853>>>>>    
82853>>>>>    Procedure Construct_Object
82855>>>>>        Forward Send Construct_Object
82857>>>>>        Move Self to ghoSQLConnectionHandler
82858>>>>>        
82858>>>>>        Property Handle phoSQLConnectionIniFile (Create(Self,RefClass(cSQLConnectionIniFile))) 
82859>>>>>        
82859>>>>>        // Driver default value settings:
82859>>>>>        // Note: When the object is created the corresponding values
82859>>>>>        // from the driver .int files are read.
82859>>>>>        // Sample: Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_DEFAULT_DEFAULT_NUMERIC of {driverNumber} to {StringVariable}
82859>>>>>        Property String psDriverDefaultValueASCII    ""
82860>>>>>        Property String psDriverDefaultValueBinary   ""
82861>>>>>        Property String psDriverDefaultValueDate     ""
82862>>>>>        Property String psDriverDefaultValueDateTime ""
82863>>>>>        Property String psDriverDefaultValueNumeric  ""
82864>>>>>        Property String psDriverDefaultValueText     ""
82865>>>>>        
82865>>>>>        // Driver "nullability" settings:
82865>>>>>        // Note: When the object is created the corresponding values
82865>>>>>        // from the driver .int files are read.
82865>>>>>        // Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_DEFAULT_NULLABLE_ASCII of {driverNumber} to {BooleanVariable}
82865>>>>>        Property Boolean pbDriverDefaultNullableASCII    False
82866>>>>>        Property Boolean pbDriverDefaultNullableBinary   False
82867>>>>>        Property Boolean pbDriverDefaultNullableDate     False
82868>>>>>        Property Boolean pbDriverDefaultNullableDateTime False
82869>>>>>        Property Boolean pbDriverDefaultNullableNumeric  False
82870>>>>>        Property Boolean pbDriverDefaultNullableText     False
82871>>>>>
82871>>>>>        // *** This is the central point of connection data for the Database Update Framework ***
82871>>>>>        //     It is private because the get/set version also updates the DAW/Mertech
82871>>>>>        //     driver interfaces.
82871>>>>>        //     There are also procedure/function pairs to set/get individual data members
82871>>>>>        //     of the struct they are all routed throu this struct property.
82871>>>>>        Property tSQLConnection Private.pSQLConnection
82872>>>>>
82872>>>>>    End_Procedure
82873>>>>>    
82873>>>>>    Procedure End_Construct_Object             
82875>>>>>        Boolean bReadSettings 
82875>>>>>        tSQLConnection SQLConnection 
82875>>>>>        tSQLConnection SQLConnection 
82875>>>>>
82875>>>>>        Forward Send End_Construct_Object
82877>>>>>
82877>>>>>        // Now is the time to read and apply SQL connection settings.
82877>>>>>        Get SetupSQLConnection True to SQLConnection   
82878>>>>>        // ToDo: Should we use two pSQLConnection properties; one for the "from" database (in case of not Embedded);
82878>>>>>        //       and one for the "to" database??
82878>>>>>        Set Private.pSQLConnection to SQLConnection
82879>>>>>    End_Procedure    
82880>>>>>    
82880>>>>>    // *** Properties ***
82880>>>>>    // All connection related "properties" (get/set pairs) are really done by changing the
82880>>>>>    // private.pSQLConnection struct connection property. These "properties" are 
82880>>>>>    // merely here for conveniance.
82880>>>>>    //           
82880>>>>>    // The pSQLConnection get/set are here so we have a "central hub"
82880>>>>>    // where we update data to/from the DAW & Mertech driver interfaces and this framework.
82880>>>>>    // This struct property contains all the connection data.
82880>>>>>    //
82880>>>>>    Procedure Set pSQLConnection tSQLConnection SQLConnection
82882>>>>>        Boolean bIsDaw bIsMertech bOK
82882>>>>>        
82882>>>>>        Set Private.pSQLConnection to SQLConnection 
82883>>>>>        
82883>>>>>        // When starting a program we might not have a connection id yet:
82883>>>>>        If (SQLConnection.sConnectionID = "" or SQLConnection.sDriverID = DATAFLEX_ID) Begin
82885>>>>>            Procedure_Return
82886>>>>>        End                 
82886>>>>>>
82886>>>>>        
82886>>>>>        // After we have set the class property we need to tell the DAW/Mertech
82886>>>>>        // driver interfaces about the change & make a new login.
82886>>>>>        Get SQLLogin SQLConnection to bOK
82887>>>>>        If (bOK = False) Begin
82889>>>>>            Error DFERR_PROGRAM "Login error."       
82890>>>>>>
82890>>>>>        End 
82890>>>>>>
82890>>>>>        
82890>>>>>        // Now is the time to setup our driver default values by reading the driver .int file:
82890>>>>>        Send SetupDriverDefaults SQLConnection.sDriverID
82891>>>>>        
82891>>>>>    End_Procedure                 
82892>>>>>    
82892>>>>>    // Similar to _SqlCheckCurrentDriver but generates no error and it doesn't 
82892>>>>>    // attempt to load the driver.
82892>>>>>    // Returns true if the passed driver is SQL based.        
