83410>>>>>    // This is needed when e.g. the connection id we have specified in the program code
83410>>>>>    // also exists in e.g. the MSSQLDRV.ini file (can either be local in the Data folder
83410>>>>>    // or the one in the DataFlex Bin folder.)
83410>>>>>    // We then need to delete the current one before creating a new one.
83410>>>>>    // This is because the parameters may differ between the program code and the
83410>>>>>    // MSSQLDRV.ini file in a deployed environment. Also DataFlex will generate an error
83410>>>>>    // when one tries to create a Connection ID that already exists.
83410>>>>>    Procedure RemoveExistingConnectionID String sDriverID String sConnectionID
83412>>>>>        Integer iResult iDriver iNumConn iConn
83412>>>>>        Handle hoCLI
83412>>>>>        String sID   
83412>>>>>        
83412>>>>>        If (sDriverID = "" or sConnectionID = "") Begin
83414>>>>>            Procedure_Return
83415>>>>>        End                 
83415>>>>>>
83415>>>>>        
83415>>>>>        Move 0 to iResult
83416>>>>>        Get Create U_cCLIHandler to hoCLI
83417>>>>>        If (hoCLI <> 0) Begin
83419>>>>>            Set psDriverID of hoCLI to sDriverID   
83420>>>>>            Get DriverIndex sDriverID to iDriver
83421>>>>>            Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_NUMBER_CONNECTION_IDS of iDriver to iNumConn 
83424>>>>>            Decrement iNumConn
83425>>>>>            For iConn from 0 to iNumConn
83431>>>>>>
83431>>>>>                Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_CONNECTION_ID of iDriver iConn to sID
83434>>>>>                If (Uppercase(sID) = Uppercase(sConnectionID)) Begin
83436>>>>>                    Get DeleteConnectionID of hoCLI sConnectionID -1 to iResult
83437>>>>>                End
83437>>>>>>
83437>>>>>            Loop
83438>>>>>>
83438>>>>>            Send Destroy of hoCLI
83439>>>>>        End
83439>>>>>>
83439>>>>>    
83439>>>>>    End_Procedure   
