91088>>>// Notice      :
91088>>>// $Author(s)  : John Tuohy
91088>>>//
91088>>>// $Rev History
91088>>>//
91088>>>// JT 06/27/97   File created
91088>>>//************************************************************************
91088>>>
91088>>>// This provides a quick and simple way to create an about package for a program.
91088>>>// You need to create a message inside you client area called Activate_About.
91088>>>// Within this message you should send the message DoAbout passing needed
91088>>>// string information.
91088>>>//
91088>>>//       Procedure Activate_About
91088>>>//           Send DoAbout sTitle sVersion sCopyright sAuthor sBitmap
91088>>>//       End_Procedure
91088>>>//    where: sTitle =     Name of application. If none provided, uses caption
91088>>>//                        bar title
91088>>>//           sVersion   = Version Line. If none provided, will be blank
91088>>>//           sCopyRight = Copyright Line. If none provided, will be blank
91088>>>//           sAuthor    = Author name, blank if none provided
91088>>>//           sBitMap    = Bitmap logo. If none provided, standard VDF bitmap
91088>>>//                        is used.
91088>>>// It is expected that you will place this in your own object package. For
91088>>>// example an order about package may look like this:
91088>>>//
91088>>>//   // OrderAbout.pkg
91088>>>//   Use StdAbout.pkg
91088>>>//   Procedure Activate_About
91088>>>//      String sTitle sCopyright sVersion sAuthor
91088>>>//      Move "My Order Entry System" to sTitle
91088>>>//      Move "Version 2.1" to sVersion
91088>>>//      Move "Copyright 1997, Super Software Inc." to sCopyright
91088>>>//      Move "John Smith"  to sAuthor
91088>>>//      Send DoAbout sTitle sVersion sCopyright sAuthor ""
91088>>>//   end_procedure
91088>>>//   // end of file.
91088>>>
91088>>>Use DfAbout.pkg
Including file: DfAbout.pkg    (C:\Projects\DF18\DbUpdateFramework\AppSrc\DfAbout.pkg)
