91374>>>>>>>>>>>
91374>>>>>>>>>>>// Help System Package
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//
91374>>>>>>>>>>>// Public Properties that should be set:
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//     Property String  Help_Filename   (Help_File_Default(self))
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//     Property Integer Help_Id_General 0
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//     Property Integer Help_Id_Index   0
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//     Property Integer Help_Id_Keys    0
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//     Property Integer Help_Id_Files   0
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//     Property Integer Help_Id_Errors  0
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//
91374>>>>>>>>>>>// Public messsages which are sent to this object:
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//    procedure View_Context_KeyWord_Help integer Obj
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//    procedure View_Context_ID_Help      integer Obj
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//    procedure View_Context_Help         integer Obj
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//    procedure View_Help_for_help        integer Obj
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//    procedure View_help_index           integer Obj
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//    procedure View_Keys_Help            integer Obj
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//    procedure View_File_Help            integer Obj
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//    procedure View_Error_Help           integer Obj
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//    procedure View_Help_on_Topic        integer Obj
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//
91374>>>>>>>>>>>// Protected Messages:
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//        These messages invoke the Window's help system and are not
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//        directly sent by outside objects. They are sent by public
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//        "view_xxx" messages and might be used if you are creating
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//        a sub-class of an object-class.
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//    Procedure Exec_System_Context_Help  integer Context_id
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//    Procedure Exec_System_Help          string  Keyword
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//    Procedure Exec_Context_Help         string  Context
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//    Functions for converting DF help IDs to windows Help Ids
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//        Any of these can return either a string or an integer.
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//    Function System_Help_Context_id Integer ID Returns String
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//           Convert a DF help context id into a windows id. By default,
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//           just return the same value (a one to one match). This is called
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//           by View_Context_id_help and View_Context_Help
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//    Function System_Help_File_Id Integer File# Integer Field# Returns String
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//           Convert file and field into a help id. By default it returns the
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//           file#. Called by View_File_Help.
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//    Function System_Help_Error_id Integer Id Returns String
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//           Convert an error message into an ID. Right now it returns the
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//           the general error context id property, Help_id_errors. This
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//           will invoke general error help. If you want error support at the
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//           error# level you will have to determine the program to help
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//           interface yourself. Errors have a very large range and it is
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//           therefore hard to come up with an automatic numbering scheme.
91374>>>>>>>>>>>//           Called by View_Error_Help.
91374>>>>>>>>>>>
91374>>>>>>>>>>>
91374>>>>>>>>>>>Use Windows.pkg
91374>>>>>>>>>>>Use WinHlp.pkg // low level help call to windows API provides global message gDoWinHelp
91374>>>>>>>>>>>Use HelpSystemConstants.pkg // constants used by help system
91374>>>>>>>>>>>
91374>>>>>>>>>>>Register_Function phoWorkspace Returns Handle
91374>>>>>>>>>>>Register_function peHelpType  returns integer
91374>>>>>>>>>>>
91374>>>>>>>>>>>class HelpSystem is an cObject
91375>>>>>>>>>>>
91375>>>>>>>>>>>    register_function Help_File_Default returns string
91375>>>>>>>>>>>
91375>>>>>>>>>>>    procedure Construct_Object
91377>>>>>>>>>>>       Forward send Construct_Object
91379>>>>>>>>>>>
91379>>>>>>>>>>>       // Help file name only. If set, this overrides all other settings.
91379>>>>>>>>>>>       Property String psHelpFile
91380>>>>>>>>>>>
91380>>>>>>>>>>>       // Help_FileName
91380>>>>>>>>>>>       //   full path name of Help file. The default value grabs its value
91380>>>>>>>>>>>       //   from .ini or environment settings. See functiob Help_file_Default
91380>>>>>>>>>>>       //
91380>>>>>>>>>>>       Property String  Private.Help_Filename (Help_File_Default(self))
91381>>>>>>>>>>>
91381>>>>>>>>>>>       // The following properties are the default values for the help files
91381>>>>>>>>>>>       // IDs for the various subjects. Setting these requires an agreement
91381>>>>>>>>>>>       // between the DF help system and the help file.
91381>>>>>>>>>>>       //
91381>>>>>>>>>>>       Property Integer Help_Id_General  0
91382>>>>>>>>>>>       Property Integer Help_Id_Index    0
91383>>>>>>>>>>>       Property Integer Help_Id_Keys     0
91384>>>>>>>>>>>       Property Integer Help_Id_Files    0
91385>>>>>>>>>>>       Property Integer Help_Id_Errors   0
91386>>>>>>>>>>>
91386>>>>>>>>>>>       // this is now the default help object
91386>>>>>>>>>>>       Move self to Help_Object_id
91387>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Procedure
91388>>>>>>>>>>>
91388>>>>>>>>>>>   // New rules for VDF8:
91388>>>>>>>>>>>   // 1. If psHelpFile exists, find the file in the file path and use it
91388>>>>>>>>>>>   // 2. If application object exists and help type is windows, use psHelpFile from there, find in file path and use it.
91388>>>>>>>>>>>   // 3. If no help file exists, use thge old private help name (which gets the full name from the registry -only if no app object)
91388>>>>>>>>>>>   //    Last method is deprecated and only used for old applications
91388>>>>>>>>>>>   //
91388>>>>>>>>>>>   Function Help_filename returns string
91390>>>>>>>>>>>        string sHelpName
91390>>>>>>>>>>>        // If ghoWorkSpace Get Help_FileName of ghoWorkSpace to sHelpName // removed for VDF8
91390>>>>>>>>>>>
91390>>>>>>>>>>>        // If an Application object is used, take the name from there.
91390>>>>>>>>>>>        Get psHelpFile to sHelpName
91391>>>>>>>>>>>        If (sHelpName="" AND ghoApplication AND peHelpType(ghoApplication)=htWinHelp) Begin
91393>>>>>>>>>>>            Get psHelpFile of ghoApplication To sHelpName
91394>>>>>>>>>>>            //Move (psHelpPath(phoWorkspace(ghoApplication)) -"\" -sHelpName) To sHelpName
91394>>>>>>>>>>>        End
91394>>>>>>>>>>>>
91394>>>>>>>>>>>        If (sHelpName<>"") begin
91396>>>>>>>>>>>            Get_File_Path sHelpName To sHelpName
91397>>>>>>>>>>>            Function_Return sHelpName
91398>>>>>>>>>>>        end
91398>>>>>>>>>>>>
91398>>>>>>>>>>>        // if not set anywhere (and ideally it is) we use this.
91398>>>>>>>>>>>        Get Private.Help_FileName to sHelpName
91399>>>>>>>>>>>        Function_Return sHelpName
91400>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Function
91401>>>>>>>>>>>
91401>>>>>>>>>>>    Procedure Set Help_FileName string sName
91403>>>>>>>>>>>        Set Private.Help_FileName to sName
91404>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Procedure
91405>>>>>>>>>>>
91405>>>>>>>>>>>
91405>>>>>>>>>>>
91405>>>>>>>>>>>    // Consider this message PRIVATE in that it should only be changed
91405>>>>>>>>>>>    // by a sub-class and not an object. It is called in construct_object
91405>>>>>>>>>>>    // before it knows about object augmentations!!!!
91405>>>>>>>>>>>    //
91405>>>>>>>>>>>    //  Sets the Help_file_name by looking at the .INI file for:
91405>>>>>>>>>>>    //        HELP_DIR    - help directory (will check environment variable
91405>>>>>>>>>>>    //                      windir if not found - avoid this usage). If not
91405>>>>>>>>>>>    //                      blank append "\" as required.
91405>>>>>>>>>>>    //
91405>>>>>>>>>>>    //        HELP_FILE   - help file name. If blank uses the default help
91405>>>>>>>>>>>    //                      file name
91405>>>>>>>>>>>    //
91405>>>>>>>>>>>    Function Help_File_Default Returns String
91407>>>>>>>>>>>       String HelpFileDir HelpFileName sSubKey
91407>>>>>>>>>>>       // if using the application object we expect the help name to be
91407>>>>>>>>>>>       // defined in the application object or directly in the help object. No Exceptions
91407>>>>>>>>>>>       If (ghoApplication) function_return ""
91410>>>>>>>>>>>
91410>>>>>>>>>>>       // else if no application (and hence no WS) use an old deprecated method of checking
91410>>>>>>>>>>>       // for the module name in local_machine.
91410>>>>>>>>>>>       Get Module_name of Desktop to sSubKey
91411>>>>>>>>>>>       Get_Profile_String sSubKey HELP_DIR to HelpFileDir
91414>>>>>>>>>>>       Get_Profile_String sSubKey HELP_FILE to HelpFileName
91417>>>>>>>>>>>       // if dir exists, sure it has a "\" at the end. If no directory the
91417>>>>>>>>>>>       // dir must be blank so current directory is searched
91417>>>>>>>>>>>       If ( (HelpFileDir<>'') AND (Right(HelpFileDir,1)<>"\") ) ;          Move (HelpFileDir - '\') to HelpFileDir
91420>>>>>>>>>>>       If HelpFileName eq '' Move DEFAULT_HELP_FILENAME to HelpFileName
91423>>>>>>>>>>>       Function_Return (HelpFileDir - HelpFileName)
91424>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Function
91425>>>>>>>>>>>
91425>>>>>>>>>>>    // The System_Help_xxxx messages convert a DF help integer ID into
91425>>>>>>>>>>>    // a context value that can be used by the windows help system. If
91425>>>>>>>>>>>    // you return a number or a string. Numbers will get used for context ID
91425>>>>>>>>>>>    // help, non-numbers get used for keyword context help
91425>>>>>>>>>>>
91425>>>>>>>>>>>    // By default return ID passed. This creates a direct mapping between
91425>>>>>>>>>>>    // context IDs in your object and the context IDs in windows help.
91425>>>>>>>>>>>    //
91425>>>>>>>>>>>    Function System_Help_Context_id Integer ID Returns String
91427>>>>>>>>>>>       Function_Return ID
91428>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Function // System_Help_Context_id
91429>>>>>>>>>>>
91429>>>>>>>>>>>    // Returns the file# which assumes that we have a direct mapping between
91429>>>>>>>>>>>    // the file number and a window's help context_id. We are ignoring field#
91429>>>>>>>>>>>    // in this case (although your augmentation would not have to). If the
91429>>>>>>>>>>>    // file# is 0, return a the HELP_ID context id.
91429>>>>>>>>>>>    //
91429>>>>>>>>>>>    Function System_Help_File_Id Integer File# Integer Field# Returns String
91431>>>>>>>>>>>       String rVal
91431>>>>>>>>>>>       if File# eq 0 Move (Help_id_files(self)) to rVal
91434>>>>>>>>>>>       Else Move File# to rVal
91436>>>>>>>>>>>       Function_Return Rval
91437>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Function // System_Help_File_id
91438>>>>>>>>>>>
91438>>>>>>>>>>>    // Convert an error id into a help context id. Return the general
91438>>>>>>>>>>>    // Help id property value. We do this because error number have
91438>>>>>>>>>>>    // a rather large range (1-9000) and just using the number would consume
91438>>>>>>>>>>>    // too much of the context id space.
91438>>>>>>>>>>>    //
91438>>>>>>>>>>>    Function System_Help_Error_id Integer Id Returns String
91440>>>>>>>>>>>       Function_Return (Help_Id_Errors(self))
91441>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Function // System_Help_Error_id
91442>>>>>>>>>>>
91442>>>>>>>>>>>    // Use this if you want your help context to be keyword based
91442>>>>>>>>>>>    //
91442>>>>>>>>>>>    procedure View_Context_KeyWord_Help integer Obj
91444>>>>>>>>>>>       String Context
91444>>>>>>>>>>>       If Obj gt 0 ;          Get Help_Context of obj HELP_CONTEXT_KEYWORD to Context
91447>>>>>>>>>>>       Send Exec_System_Help Context
