91479>>>>>>>>>>>    Procedure View_File_Help Integer Obj
91481>>>>>>>>>>>       String Context FilFld
91481>>>>>>>>>>>       Integer File# Field# Dot
91481>>>>>>>>>>>       If Obj gt 0 Begin
91483>>>>>>>>>>>          // This should return the file and field as a string in
91483>>>>>>>>>>>          // FFF.fff format (F=File, f=format).
91483>>>>>>>>>>>          Get Help_Context of Obj HELP_CONTEXT_DATAFILE to FilFld
91484>>>>>>>>>>>          // Parse FilFld into File# and Field#.
91484>>>>>>>>>>>          Pos '.' in FilFld to Dot
91486>>>>>>>>>>>>
91486>>>>>>>>>>>          if Dot ne 0 begin
91488>>>>>>>>>>>             Left FilFld to File#  (dot-1)
91490>>>>>>>>>>>>
91490>>>>>>>>>>>             Mid  FilFld to Field# 255 (dot+1)
91493>>>>>>>>>>>>
91493>>>>>>>>>>>          End
91493>>>>>>>>>>>>
91493>>>>>>>>>>>       End
91493>>>>>>>>>>>>
91493>>>>>>>>>>>       Get System_Help_File_id File# Field# to Context
91494>>>>>>>>>>>       Send Exec_Context_Help Context
91495>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Procedure // View_File_Help
91496>>>>>>>>>>>
91496>>>>>>>>>>>    //  View help on an error. Current version uses context id help.
